article.headline: Charleston Southern 75, Coastal Carolina 64
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Mathiang Muo scored 17 points to lead Charleston Southern to a 75-64 victory over Coastal Carolina to claim the Big South Conference's regular-season championship on Saturday in the regular-season finale for both. Arlon Harper and Saah Nimley had 15 points each for Charleston Southern (17-11, 12-4), which ended a two-game losing streak. Charleston Southern shot 45.2 percent from the field (28 of 62) and made 15 of 34 3-pointers. Anthony Raffa scored 23 points and Warren Gillis 19 for the Chanticleers (14-14, 9-7), who shot 48 percent (24 of 50) but managed only 3 of 16 of their 3-point shots. Charleston Southern led 38-30 at halftime, and a 15-6 run to open the second half pushed its advantage to 53-36 on Tristian Curtis' layup with 12:16 remaining. The Buccaneers stretched the lead to 20 points at 61-41 on Paul Gombwer's layup with 10:45 left and were never threatened.
